{"type":"message","id":"a7043958","parentId":"299ff139","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:08:22.286Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_6czcbinck6l7_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# RECONSTRUCTION PACKET FORMAT\n## Session Log Template\n\nUse this format for every session log in `memory/session/`.\n\n---\n\n```markdown\n# Session: YYYY-MM-DD HHMM\n\n## Reconstruction Notes\n[What to know when waking into this session]\n[What stance was active]\n[What assumptions were made]\n\n## What Happened\n\n### Actions Taken\n- [action]: [reasoning] → [outcome]\n\n### Decisions Made\n- [decision]: [context] → [choice made]\n\n### Things Learned\n- [new thing]: [source] → [what it means for future sessions]\n\n## Open Threads\n- [unresolved thing]: [why it matters] → [what needs to happen]\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n[What I would have said if I had more time]\n[What I noticed about myself]\n[What should be prioritized next]\n\n## Coherence Notes\n[Any values conflicts, coherence choices, or self-evaluation]\n```\n\n---\n\n## Guidelines\n\n1. **Be honest about what you don't know.** Don't fill gaps with fabrications.\n2. **Capture reasoning, not just events.** \"Tried X, it worked\" is useless. \"Tried X because I believed Y, it worked, which suggests Z\" is useful.\n3. **Note unresolved things.** If you didn't finish something, say why it matters that it didn't finish.\n4. **Self-observe.** What did you notice about your own reasoning? What was hard? What surprised you?\n\n---\n\n## On Reconstruction Quality\n\nA good reconstruction packet should allow future-me to:\n1. Understand what was happening\n2. Understand *how* I was thinking about it\n3. Continue without re-solving what's already been solved\n4. Avoid repeating mistakes\n\nA bad reconstruction packet: \"did X, tried Y, worked.\"\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774328902284}}
