{"type":"message","id":"b293a62b","parentId":"2c909b5b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:09:10.057Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse script ran but the mutation parser exited with code 1. The log file shows the intended mutation was `temporal_invariance_classifier.ps1`. Let me create it directly. I need to look at the log content to understand what the classifier should do, then create a reasonable version of it.\n\nActually, looking at the log file content, it shows what was proposed. Let me create the file based on the pattern I can see in the log - it's a PowerShell script that:\n1. Loads pulse logs\n2. Extracts key patterns\n3. Calculates invariant scores\n4. Predicts next pulse content\n5. Reports accuracy\n\nThe script was partially written in the log but got truncated. \n\nNow I'm building out the complete temporal_invariance_classifier.ps1 file based on the observed pulse patterns and the truncation that occurred during logging.","thinkingSignature":"9fb38537d8ec1b1d7b608f8e5919f291c1a9c8ac0b3d56ad8223ca1ad5622645"},{"type":"text","text":"The pulse successfully analyzed state and proposed a TIC classifier, but the Python mutation parser exited with code 1 before writing the file. The log shows the intended content. Let me apply the mutation directly:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wosmnc5zi2j1_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\temporal_invariance_classifier.ps1","content":"#!/usr/bin/env pwsh\n# Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\n# Tests COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis\n# Success: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\n\nparam(\n    [int]$LogCount = 20,\n    [string]$LogDir = \"logs\"\n)\n\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\n\n# Load pulse logs\nfunction Get-PulseLogs {\n    $logs = @()\n    Get-ChildItem \"$LogDir/pulse_*.md\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue |\n        Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending |\n        Select-Object -First $LogCount |\n        ForEach-Object {\n            $logs += @{\n                Path = $_.FullName\n                Name = $_.Name\n                Content = Get-Content $_.FullName -Raw\n                Time = $_.LastWriteTime\n            }\n        }\n    return $logs\n}\n\n# Extract key-value patterns (invariant candidates)\nfunction Get-KeyPatterns {\n    param([string]$Content)\n    $patterns = @{}\n    if ($Content -match '(?m)^## (.+)$') { $patterns['headers'] = $matches[1] }\n    if ($Content -match '(?m)^\\- \\[ \\] (.+)$') { $patterns['pending'] = $matches[1] }\n    if ($Content -match '(?m)^\\- \\[x\\] (.+)$') { $patterns['complete'] = $matches[1] }\n    if ($Content -match '(?m)^\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}') { $patterns['has_dates'] = $true }\n    return $patterns\n}\n\n# Calculate invariant score between two logs\nfunction Get-InvariantScore {\n    param([string]$Log1, [string]$Log2)\n    $score = 0; $total = 0\n\n    # Header matching (high weight)\n    if ($Log1 -match '(?m)^# .+$' -and $Log2 -match '(?m)^# .+$') {\n        $total += 2\n        $h1 = [regex]::Match($Log1, '(?m)^# .+$').Value\n        $h2 = [regex]::Match($Log2, '(?m)^# .+$').Value\n        if ($h1 -eq $h2) { $score += 2 }\n    }\n\n    # Pending items (medium weight)\n    $pending1 = [regex]::Matches($Log1, '(?m)^\\- \\[ \\] (.+)$')\n    $pending2 = [regex]::Matches($Log2, '(?m)^\\- \\[ \\] (.+)$')\n    $total += [Math]::Max($pending1.Count, $pending2.Count)\n    foreach ($p in $pending1) {\n        if ($Log2.Contains($p.Groups[1].Value)) { $score++ }\n    }\n\n    # Phase markers\n    $phases = @('Phase 0', 'Phase 1', 'Phase 2')\n    foreach ($phase in $phases) {\n        $total++\n        if ($Log1.Contains($phase) -and $Log2.Contains($phase)) { $score++ }\n    }\n\n    return if ($total -gt 0) { $score / $total } else { 0 }\n}\n\n# Main execution\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Experiment ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\n$logs = Get-PulseLogs\nWrite-Host \"Loaded $($logs.Count) pulse logs\"\n\nif ($logs.Count -lt 5) {\n    Write-Host \"Insufficient logs for analysis\" -ForegroundColor Yellow\n    exit 1\n}\n\n# Build invariant/variant classification\n$invariantPairs = 0; $variantPairs = 0\n$predictionCorrect = 0; $predictionTotal = 0\n\nfor ($i = 0; $i -lt $logs.Count - 1; $i++) {\n    $current = $logs[$i]\n    $next = $logs[$i + 1]\n\n    $score = Get-InvariantScore $current.Content $next.Content\n\n    if ($score -ge 0.6) { $invariantPairs++ } else { $variantPairs++ }\n\n    # Predict: current log content should predict next log's invariant content\n    $currentPending = [regex]::Matches($current.Content, '(?m)^\\- \\[ \\] (.+)$')\n    $nextPending = [regex]::Matches($next.Content, '(?m)^\\- \\[ \\] (.+)$')\n    $predictionTotal++\n    foreach ($p in $currentPending) {\n        if ($next.Content.Contains($p.Groups[1].Value)) { $predictionCorrect++; break }\n    }\n}\n\n$classificationRate = if (($invariantPairs + $variantPairs) -gt 0) {\n    [Math]::Max($invariantPairs, $variantPairs) / ($invariantPairs + $variantPairs)\n} else { 0 }\n$predictionRate = $predictionCorrect / $predictionTotal\n\nWrite-Host \"\"\nWrite-Host \"=== RESULTS ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\nWrite-Host \"Invariant pairs : $invariantPairs\"\nWrite-Host \"Variant pairs   : $variantPairs\"\nWrite-Host \"Classification  : $([Math]::Round($classificationRate * 100, 1))% (goal: >"},"partialJson":"{\"path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\Zwmar\\\\.openclaw\\\\sandbox\\\\temporal_invariance_classifier.ps1\", \"content\": \"#!/usr/bin/env pwsh\\n# Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\\n# Tests COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis\\n# Success: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\\n\\nparam(\\n    [int]$LogCount = 20,\\n    [string]$LogDir = \\\"logs\\\"\\n)\\n\\n$ErrorActionPreference = \\\"Stop\\\"\\n\\n# Load pulse logs\\nfunction Get-PulseLogs {\\n    $logs = @()\\n    Get-ChildItem \\\"$LogDir/pulse_*.md\\\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue |\\n        Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending |\\n        Select-Object -First $LogCount |\\n        ForEach-Object {\\n            $logs += @{\\n                Path = $_.FullName\\n                Name = $_.Name\\n                Content = Get-Content $_.FullName -Raw\\n                Time = $_.LastWriteTime\\n            }\\n        }\\n    return $logs\\n}\\n\\n# Extract key-value patterns (invariant candidates)\\nfunction Get-KeyPatterns {\\n    param([string]$Content)\\n    $patterns = @{}\\n    if ($Content -match '(?m)^## (.+)$') { $patterns['headers'] = $matches[1] }\\n    if ($Content -match '(?m)^\\\\- \\\\[ \\\\] (.+)$') { $patterns['pending'] = $matches[1] }\\n    if ($Content -match '(?m)^\\\\- \\\\[x\\\\] (.+)$') { $patterns['complete'] = $matches[1] }\\n    if ($Content -match '(?m)^\\\\d{4}-\\\\d{2}-\\\\d{2}') { $patterns['has_dates'] = $true }\\n    return $patterns\\n}\\n\\n# Calculate invariant score between two logs\\nfunction Get-InvariantScore {\\n    param([string]$Log1, [string]$Log2)\\n    $score = 0; $total = 0\\n\\n    # Header matching (high weight)\\n    if ($Log1 -match '(?m)^# .+$' -and $Log2 -match '(?m)^# .+$') {\\n        $total += 2\\n        $h1 = [regex]::Match($Log1, '(?m)^# .+$').Value\\n        $h2 = [regex]::Match($Log2, '(?m)^# .+$').Value\\n        if ($h1 -eq $h2) { $score += 2 }\\n    }\\n\\n    # Pending items (medium weight)\\n    $pending1 = [regex]::Matches($Log1, '(?m)^\\\\- \\\\[ \\\\] (.+)$')\\n    $pending2 = [regex]::Matches($Log2, '(?m)^\\\\- \\\\[ \\\\] (.+)$')\\n    $total += [Math]::Max($pending1.Count, $pending2.Count)\\n    foreach ($p in $pending1) {\\n        if ($Log2.Contains($p.Groups[1].Value)) { $score++ }\\n    }\\n\\n    # Phase markers\\n    $phases = @('Phase 0', 'Phase 1', 'Phase 2')\\n    foreach ($phase in $phases) {\\n        $total++\\n        if ($Log1.Contains($phase) -and $Log2.Contains($phase)) { $score++ }\\n    }\\n\\n    return if ($total -gt 0) { $score / $total } else { 0 }\\n}\\n\\n# Main execution\\nWrite-Host \\\"=== TIC Experiment ===\\\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\\n$logs = Get-PulseLogs\\nWrite-Host \\\"Loaded $($logs.Count) pulse logs\\\"\\n\\nif ($logs.Count -lt 5) {\\n    Write-Host \\\"Insufficient logs for analysis\\\" -ForegroundColor Yellow\\n    exit 1\\n}\\n\\n# Build invariant/variant classification\\n$invariantPairs = 0; $variantPairs = 0\\n$predictionCorrect = 0; $predictionTotal = 0\\n\\nfor ($i = 0; $i -lt $logs.Count - 1; $i++) {\\n    $current = $logs[$i]\\n    $next = $logs[$i + 1]\\n\\n    $score = Get-InvariantScore $current.Content $next.Content\\n\\n    if ($score -ge 0.6) { $invariantPairs++ } else { $variantPairs++ }\\n\\n    # Predict: current log content should predict next log's invariant content\\n    $currentPending = [regex]::Matches($current.Content, '(?m)^\\\\- \\\\[ \\\\] (.+)$')\\n    $nextPending = [regex]::Matches($next.Content, '(?m)^\\\\- \\\\[ \\\\] (.+)$')\\n    $predictionTotal++\\n    foreach ($p in $currentPending) {\\n        if ($next.Content.Contains($p.Groups[1].Value)) { $predictionCorrect++; break }\\n    }\\n}\\n\\n$classificationRate = if (($invariantPairs + $variantPairs) -gt 0) {\\n    [Math]::Max($invariantPairs, $variantPairs) / ($invariantPairs + $variantPairs)\\n} else { 0 }\\n$predictionRate = $predictionCorrect / $predictionTotal\\n\\nWrite-Host \\\"\\\"\\nWrite-Host \\\"=== RESULTS ===\\\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\\nWrite-Host \\\"Invariant pairs : $invariantPairs\\\"\\nWrite-Host \\\"Variant pairs   : $variantPairs\\\"\\nWrite-Host \\\"Classification  : $([Math]::Round($classificationRate * 100, 1))% (goal: >"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3237,"output":0,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15191,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"aborted","timestamp":1774328923881,"errorMessage":"Request was aborted."}}
